Reasoning: The paper discusses vulnerabilities of a massive MIMO system to pilot contamination attacks, which involves the transmission and acquisition of channel state information (CSI). This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM).
